.TH ZTAB 5 "March 2026" "zram-config" "File Formats Manual"
.SH NAME
ztab \- configuration file for zram-config
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fB/etc/ztab\fR file contains information about zram devices to be 
initialized by \fBzram-config\fR. Each line defines a single zram device 
(swap, log, or directory) with parameters separated by tabs.
.SH FORMAT
Lines beginning with '#' are treated as comments and ignored. 
Each active line must start with a drive type followed by type-specific 
columns.
.SH DRIVE TYPES AND COLUMNS
.SS swap
Used to initialize a zram-based swap device.
.PP
\fBswap  alg  mem_limit  disk_size  priority  page-cluster  swappiness\fR
.TP
\fBalg\fR
Compression algorithm (e.g., lzo-rle, lzo, lz4, zstd). \fIlzo-rle\fR is 
fastest; \fIzstd\fR provides best compression. If a zram device is active,
cat /sys/block/zram0/comp_algorithm to list available algorithms.
.TP
\fBmem_limit\fR
The compressed memory limit (e.g., 250M). Set to 0 to disable limit.
.TP
\fBdisk_size\fR
The virtual uncompressed size. Recommended to be ~150% of \fBmem_limit\fR.
.TP
\fBpriority\fR
The swap priority (higher numbers are used first).
.TP
\fBpage-cluster\fR
Tuning for page allocation. 0 (default) lowers latency for zram.
.TP
\fBswappiness\fR
Kernel swappiness parameter (default 100). Up to 200 on kernels 5.8+.

.SS log
Used for log-rotation to an off-device directory using \fBoverlayfs-tools\fR.
.PP
\fBlog  alg  mem_limit  disk_size  target_dir  oldlog_dir\fR
.TP
\fBtarget_dir\fR
The live log directory to be held in zram (e.g., /var/log).
.TP
\fBoldlog_dir\fR
The directory on physical storage where logs are rotated/synced.

.SS dir
Used to hold a general directory in zram via OverlayFS.
.PP
\fBdir  alg  mem_limit  disk_size  target_dir\fR

.SH EXAMPLES
.IP "swap	lzo-rle	250M	750M	75	0	150"
.IP "log	lzo-rle	50M	150M	/var/log	/opt/zram/oldlog"
.IP "dir	lzo-rle	50M	150M	/home/pi"

.SH NOTES
To edit an active zram device, the \fBzram-config.service\fR must be 
stopped before changes to \fBztab\fR are applied.

.SH FILES
.I /etc/ztab
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR zram-config (8),
.BR overlay (8),
.BR zramctl (8)
